## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of online resources and the potential bias in historical interpretations. The lack of primary sources and the reliance on secondary analyses may affect the comprehensiveness of the findings. Additionally, the complexity of international relations and the multitude of factors leading to World War II mean that the League of Nations' role is just one aspect of a broader historical context.